   <text:p text:style-name="P53">a short wait. We were assigned rooms just underneath the one we had before. We found the place much cleaner than when we were here in November. At present we are much over- crowded, 15 in a room but we are told we will have another room assigned to the platoon when the remaining 6 of the Cheshire T moves off. We had to hang about the barracks till after 6 o&apos;clock not getting grub till 5:45. Well- 6 30 I went out into the town with Sgt. MA a Capper had a look round the town brushing up with a Whush &amp; back to barracks at 8:30. When orders came just before 10. I heard I had to parade at 8 in the morning with cleaned for Examining Post with 3 men. April 3 Up at 3:30 had to hustle round but got ready Saturday in good time. Had a quick guards parade with guards from the Chesures to conduct us to our various posts. My post was at a canal lock. To Haul Port a quiet spot, we have to stop all people going in and out and examine their passes A French guard is on watch to examine the </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P54">My Effort</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P48">a short weight we were arrange rooms just under is the one we had before. We found the place much cleaner than when we were here November all stop at present we are much overcrowded 15 around but let’s hope we will have another room arranged assigned to the Taliban to when the remaining of the Cheshire team moves off. We had to hang around about the barracks till after six o’clock but getting grub till 545.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P48"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P48">At 630 I went out into the town with green MFA and copier Cooper copper had a look around the town finished up with a whiskey back in the barracks at 830.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P48"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P48">When orders came just before 10 I heard I had to parade at eight in the more morning with buttons cleaned for an examination post with three men.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P48"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P48"><text:span text:style-name="T13">3/4/15 </text:span>Saturday</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P48"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P48">Up at 530 had to bustle around but got ready in good time.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P48"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P48">Heather quick guards Parade with regards from the gestures to conduct us to our various ports might post was at Canal lock their hope on to a quiet spot we have stopped all people going in and out and examine their passes have French guards on with us with to examine the</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P55"><text:span text:style-name="T98">I/p</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T99">20</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P56">natives. The guard room is an <text:span text:style-name="T100">estaminet</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T81">quite</text:span> a nice place attached to I bakehouse.<text:span text:style-name="T81">Then</text:span> expect us to do our own cooking but are very good in giving us pots and pans, plates etc.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P56">We ca<text:span text:style-name="T81">use a </text:span>lot of interest among the natives, firstly because we speak their language and which apparently the Cheshire<text:span text:style-name="T81">s</text:span> never attempted to do. We have had <text:span text:style-name="T81">admiring</text:span> grounds of youngsters <text:span text:style-name="T81">all</text:span> around us on this account the little girls ask us if we are engaged the boys demanding cigarettes. Although the road traffic is not great there is plenty doing on the canal. <text:span text:style-name="T81">I</text:span>t was a beastly day d<text:span text:style-name="T81">rilling</text:span> all the time but we are quite happy green especially enjoys telling to his Frenchman and is at the present m<text:span text:style-name="T81">arching</text:span> up and down with <text:span text:style-name="T81">the </text:span>French century, both at the slope <text:span text:style-name="T100">L’wntarte Corviale</text:span> personified.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P56"><text:span text:style-name="T101">Directly</text:span> we began to cook <text:span text:style-name="T81">our </text:span>dinner in the evening the lady of the house decided to have <text:span text:style-name="T81">her Saturday </text:span>clean so <text:span text:style-name="T81">G</text:span>reen and I had to feed with our heels in the air while <text:span text:style-name="T81">she</text:span> swill<text:span text:style-name="T81">s</text:span> the floor down with buckets of water, eventually we <text:span text:style-name="T81">were</text:span> compelled to </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P56"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P57"><text:span text:style-name="T98">I/p</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T99">21</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P58"><text:s/>shift our p<text:span text:style-name="T69">itch</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P58"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P58">As regards our duties we manage very well expect set that major Clark found our buttons undone and in the evening when he came round I gave giving the command to present having guards the word present out I stopped said also you were thinking that we were at wrong is being part retreat past retreat however he said he was <text:span text:style-name="T69">the</text:span> grand round rains and it was all night so we went on with it.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P58"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P58">April 4 Easter Sunday</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P58"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P58">We got back to barracks about 10 and after this dismissing my <text:span text:style-name="T69">Guard</text:span> I went off to the holy Communion at 1050 with hills cop and my drug and while Walch</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P58"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P58">Have a look around the town in afternoon and was very favorably impressed by it. It is clean and quite interesting places the par<text:span text:style-name="T69">k</text:span> t<text:span text:style-name="T69">oo</text:span> is <text:span text:style-name="T69">very</text:span> nice</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P58"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P58">The behavior of the people is a stinking contrast of that at <text:span text:style-name="T69">Baillel</text:span>. I am not scarcely said grasping and more c<text:span text:style-name="T69">outious</text:span> in fact more French in every respect. Prices are much lower April 5</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P58"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P58">On Monday we had a for Farrah Barrick/day we had a parade at with the same but seven officer and did communication of drill after <text:span text:style-name="T69">3/4</text:span> hour</text:p>
