   <text:p text:style-name="P63">want to would not tell us what we were to do and so get on with it. They wanted to keep us there from 9 to 12 again from 2 to 4. When we found this out after working hard for an hour we back the rest of the time. Saul five German prisoners being marched through the town.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63">Sunday 18</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63">church parade service in morning and another excursion in the afternoon on the canals this time with PC hills.heard from the French sentry on number one posed about their Regiment the 140 were leaving this neighborhood tomorrow and won’t being relieved by lots the seven December have size shall see him again.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63">Williams came round in the evening and asked me I give I could volunteer to go up to the trenches for instruction. I put my name down. It appears that NCO’s are going up in the parties like the M creators have done.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63">The school has now been moved from bailout to blend equals and tomorrow engine available man has to be every available man has to be turned out for drill passing. They are to go out on a mode to buses. Rumors has it I packed it that serve French is going to inspect the battalion shortly</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P61">I/p2<text:span text:style-name="T102">8</text:span></text:p>
