   <text:p text:style-name="P63">Monday, 19 April</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63">On guard at number six examining posts with their the command. A most picturesque neighborhood not a bit post except for a joy riders. The 77’s were behaving the old Regiment the 140 as we arrived. They tell me that the poor is at Cassell.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63">I think the guard mounted ceremony is worth recording. We parade in the grand place at 8:30 NCOs on the left of the men. Then calls for mosques of guards. NCOs spring to attention like their arms full, turned to the right and marks to the required shots taken up their dressing from the Sarge of this Seo God. On the command market steady return to the right the men then have the order to march on their marks, we take up our dressing and fix and wait for the adjutant. When he arrives about 10 mins to nine he inspects the guards starting with the cc. Isis ended under April 7 what the NCO has to do in there this.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63">The inspection is rapid now and the NCO has to him move about at the double to be in time for the adjutant as he runs around their here of the guard on the right is</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P61">I/p2<text:span text:style-name="T102">9</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P64">Tues </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P64">20th</text:p>
