   <text:p text:style-name="P63"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63"><text:tab/>When I came off guard, I got <text:span text:style-name="T69">a </text:span>pa<text:span text:style-name="T69">ss</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T69">and</text:span> went out into the town to hire <text:span text:style-name="T103">a</text:span> bicycle to ride over and see M<text:span text:style-name="T69">aurice</text:span>, I got one in the <text:span text:style-name="T69">Rue d Array </text:span>close to <text:span text:style-name="T69">No4</text:span> for examining post it was not much of a machine. the saddle <text:span text:style-name="T69">was </text:span>not nearly high enough so that I could not straighten my legs, the saddle <text:span text:style-name="T103">was of </text:span>shape and very hard <text:span text:style-name="T103">and </text:span>the handlebars were very low. I had a lot of trouble with the <text:span text:style-name="T69">toe </text:span>clips on the pedals at first, but managed to bend the<text:span text:style-name="T103">m</text:span> flat.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63">As far as our <text:span text:style-name="T69">Arques</text:span> there was a broad gravel path by the side of the pav<text:span text:style-name="T69">ed road</text:span> which was quite comfortable to ride on, through that town I had to endure the cobbles but there was an long stretch of <text:span text:style-name="T103">macadam</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T103">r</text:span>oad and afterwards as far as <text:span text:style-name="T103">Niepper</text:span> to that I had to take to an extremely narrow bit of <text:span text:style-name="T69">mettaling afterwards </text:span>alongside the pa<text:span text:style-name="T103">ve</text:span>. The road was practically flat all way <text:span text:style-name="T103">the</text:span> inclined <text:span text:style-name="T103">were slight</text:span> worse like I got to the Cas<text:span text:style-name="T103">sel</text:span> railway station at 1:15 after <text:span text:style-name="T103">1 </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T104">½</text:span> hours ride and inquired there for a M<text:span text:style-name="T103">aurice</text:span> they told me he was at the <text:span text:style-name="T103">C</text:span>asino a large <text:span text:style-name="T103">building</text:span> built for <text:span text:style-name="T103">a </text:span>hotel <text:span text:style-name="T103">r</text:span>ight, <text:span text:style-name="T103">on the </text:span><text:s/>highest part of the hill. I climbed the hill. <text:span text:style-name="T103">I</text:span>t is a wonderful place rising to a great <text:span text:style-name="T103">height </text:span>out of the </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P61">I/p<text:span text:style-name="T102">30</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P65">fla<text:span text:style-name="T105">t</text:span> county which surrounds it on all sides. <text:span text:style-name="T103">T</text:span>here is a tram which connects the town with the station a distance of nearly 2 miles.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P66"><text:tab/>I found M<text:span text:style-name="T103">aurice</text:span> mak<text:span text:style-name="T103">ing</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T103">a</text:span> map seated in one of the lower rooms of the hotel. He told me that the town was the headquarters of Gen. F<text:span text:style-name="T103">ock</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T103">Commanding </text:span>the French northern army. He had charge <text:span text:style-name="T103">of </text:span><text:s/>some machine guns placed on the flat roof of the hotel and the lookout post for airplanes. I had about an hour with him looking around the place. <text:span text:style-name="T103">H</text:span>e has a s<text:span text:style-name="T103">plended</text:span> hotel bedroom on the first floor, <text:span text:style-name="T105">f</text:span>rom the roof there is a wonderful view, you can see for about 30 miles in every direction. It was a beautiful clear day and you could see <text:span text:style-name="T69">ypres</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T103">and </text:span>in the o<text:span text:style-name="T69">ther</text:span> direction Cal<text:span text:style-name="T69">ais.</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T103">Y</text:span>ou can see the sand dunes stretching along the coast and the <text:span text:style-name="T69">sea beyond</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T103">A</text:span>fter I left M<text:span text:style-name="T103">aurice</text:span> I <text:span text:style-name="T103">had</text:span> a look around the town it is of course a quaint place built <text:span text:style-name="T103">as i</text:span>t his is on the slopes of <text:span text:style-name="T103">a</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T105">h</text:span>ill, <text:span text:style-name="T103">very quite with s</text:span>ome old buildings. <text:span text:style-name="T103">T</text:span>here <text:span text:style-name="T103">are </text:span>no English troops <text:span text:style-name="T69">at all</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P63">I started back about 3:15 going down the</text:p>
