   <text:p text:style-name="P68"><text:span text:style-name="T105">h</text:span>ill the French and post tried to stop me but the back peddling brak<text:span text:style-name="T105">e</text:span> would not cut <text:span text:style-name="T105">&amp;</text:span> I had to run <text:span text:style-name="T105">i</text:span>nto a field to pull the machine up. I got a sore that I could only go for about a mile at a time <text:span text:style-name="T105">&amp;</text:span> then get off <text:span text:style-name="T105">&amp;</text:span> walk about half a kilometer. There was a headwind which made things bad however I got back again about <text:span text:style-name="T105">5.</text:span> I went out and had dinner with <text:span text:style-name="T105">Hansford</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T105">&amp;</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T105">Faulsham</text:span> at the <text:span text:style-name="T105">H</text:span>otel <text:span text:style-name="T105">du</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T105">G</text:span>rand <text:span text:style-name="T105">St Loris in</text:span> <text:s/>Rue d’ <text:span text:style-name="T105">A</text:span>rr<text:span text:style-name="T105">a</text:span>s again</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P68"><text:tab/><text:span text:style-name="T105">On </text:span>Wednesday <text:span text:style-name="T105">&amp;</text:span> Thursday I had to typical bar<text:span text:style-name="T105">rach</text:span> days paraded in any old dress at 6:3<text:span text:style-name="T105">0</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T105">for </text:span>physical drill after gunfire tea at <text:span text:style-name="T105">6 o.</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T105">P</text:span>hysical drill started <text:span text:style-name="T106">¾</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T105">hour. B</text:span>reakfast at 7:30 paraded 9:30 <text:span text:style-name="T105">&amp; </text:span>11 for two lots <text:span text:style-name="T105">1</text:span> hours company drill. As there was very few privates on <text:span text:style-name="T105">p</text:span>arade <text:span text:style-name="T105">(</text:span>all being on guard all fatigues<text:span text:style-name="T105">)</text:span> the<text:span text:style-name="T105">ir</text:span> places were taken by <text:span text:style-name="T105">roles the</text:span> NCOs w<text:span text:style-name="T105">ere</text:span> section commanders <text:span text:style-name="T105">&amp;</text:span> the <text:span text:style-name="T105">batterns</text:span> w<text:span text:style-name="T105">ere</text:span> platoon commanders drilled the company <text:span text:style-name="T105">in</text:span> turn most of them know very little about it and the whole idea of a thing is for them to learn. <text:span text:style-name="T105">W</text:span>e paraded <text:span text:style-name="T105">at</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T105">2 </text:span>to visit the range and both days is</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P61">I/p<text:span text:style-name="T102">3</text:span>2</text:p>
