   <text:p text:style-name="P68"><text:tab/>On Sunday the PC MA hills <text:span text:style-name="T107">&amp;</text:span> I went for a walk out to the <text:span text:style-name="T107">A</text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T107">ques</text:span> there is a tremendous drop <text:span text:style-name="T107">o</text:span>n the canal the<text:span text:style-name="T107">r</text:span>e, quite 60 feet. <text:span text:style-name="T107">I</text:span>t is negotiated in two ways the first is by locks of which there are <text:span text:style-name="T107">five one </text:span>opening into the other <text:span text:style-name="T107">a</text:span>long<text:span text:style-name="T107">side</text:span> this there is an curious arrangement a mechanical lift. The barges going up right into a tremendous tank which is then raised at apparatus by h<text:span text:style-name="T107">ydraulic</text:span> power at the top of the float out into large basin. It is really a wonderful arrangement <text:span text:style-name="T107">&amp; </text:span>I should like to see it working</text:p>
